Setup

# Load packages
library(broom)
library(ggrepel)
library(magrittr)
library(sandwich)
library(tidyverse)
library(treemapify)


# Import data
trials <- read_csv(
  "../../data/tidy_data/trials-ihme.csv"
)

ihme <- read_csv(
  "../../data/tidy_data/ihme.csv", 
  col_types = cols(ihme_id = col_character(), who_id = col_character())
)

who <- read_csv(
  "../../data/tidy_data/who.csv", 
  col_types = cols(ID = col_character())
)

Create dataset

# Create an appropriate IHME
ihme_dev <- 
  list(
    `More developed` = ihme,
    `Less developed` = ihme,
    `All` = ihme
  ) %>% 
  bind_rows(.id = "dev")

# Create duplicated dataset
regression <-
  trials %>% 
  mutate(dev = if_else(is_developed, "More developed", "Less developed")) %>% 
  bind_rows(trials, .id = "id_dev") %>%
  mutate(dev = if_else(id_dev == 2, "All", dev)) %>% 
  filter(is_eligible, is_classified) %>%
  separate_rows(ihme_level_three, sep = "; ") %>%
  select(-condition) %>%
  right_join(ihme_dev, by = c("ihme_level_three" = "ihme_id", "dev")) %>%
  filter(level == "level_three") %>% 
  mutate(level_three = condition) %>% 
  left_join(select(who, ID, level_two), by = c("who_id" = "ID")) %>% 
  mutate(n_sample_adjust = n_sample / n_level_three)


# Summarize values
regression %<>%
  group_by(dev, level_three, dalys) %>% 
  summarise(
    sample_size = sum(n_sample_adjust, na.rm = T),
    n_studies = sum(!is.na(n_sample)),
    n_complete_enroll = sum(str_detect(status_june23_sc, "C|E|R"), na.rm = T),
    p_complete_enroll = mean(str_detect(status_june23_sc, "C|E|R"), na.rm = T)
  ) %>% 
  mutate(complete_enroll = case_when(
    is.na(p_complete_enroll) | is.nan(p_complete_enroll)  ~ NA_character_,
    p_complete_enroll > 0.5 ~ ">50%",
    p_complete_enroll < 0.25 ~ "0-25%",
    T ~ "25-50%"
  )) %>%
  mutate(complete_enroll = factor(complete_enroll)) %>%
  mutate(complete_enroll = fct_relevel(complete_enroll, ">50%", "25-50%")) %>%
  ungroup()

Sample per development

regression %>%
  filter(dev != "All") %>% 
  group_by(dev) %>% 
  summarise(total_sample = sum(sample_size)) %>%
  mutate(p = scales::percent(total_sample / sum(total_sample), 0.1)) %>% 
  sable()

Regression analysis

Fit lines.

glm.linear <- 
  regression %>% 
  filter(dev != "All") %>% 
  mutate(dalys = dalys / 10^6) %>% 
  lm(sample_size ~ dalys + dev + dalys * dev, .)

glm.quasi <- 
  regression %>% 
  filter(dev != "All") %>% 
  mutate(dalys = dalys / 10^6) %>% 
  glm(sample_size ~ dalys + dev + dalys * dev, ., family = "quasipoisson")

glm.lognormal <- 
  regression %>% 
  filter(dev != "All") %>% 
  mutate(dalys = dalys / 10^6) %>% 
  lm(log(sample_size + 1) ~ dalys + dev + dalys * dev, data = .)

glm.gamma <- 
  regression %>% 
  filter(dev != "All") %>% 
  mutate(dalys = dalys / 10^6) %>% 
  glm(sample_size + 1 ~ dalys + dev + dalys * dev, ., family = Gamma(link = "log"))

Obtain robust results using the sandwich estimator.

# Calculate
pvals <- lmtest::coeftest(glm.linear, vcov = sandwich)
confints <- lmtest::coefci(glm.linear, vcov = sandwich)

# Construct final table
pvals %>% 
  cbind(confints) %>% 
  as.data.frame() %>% 
  rownames_to_column(var = "Variable") %>% 
  as_tibble() %>% 
  # mutate(across(c(Estimate, `2.5 %`, `97.5 %`), exp)) %>% 
  sable()
Variable Estimate Std. Error t value Pr(>|t|) 2.5 % 97.5 %
(Intercept) 4991.19 4620.58 1.08021 0.28652 -4347.36 14329.731
dalys 477.84 107.11 4.46138 0.00006 261.37 694.314
devMore developed -2620.54 5023.52 -0.52166 0.60479 -12773.45 7532.362
dalys:devMore developed -238.17 122.17 -1.94950 0.05827 -485.09 8.744

This is a descriptive model, not a model appropriate for prediction or inference. Overall, with every million DALYs, there was a mean increase in total sample size ranging from 261 to 694 (Sandwich p-value, 0.00006). Even though, overall, the mean total sample size in more developed countries was smaller than that of less developed countries, these data do not suggest a simple linear relationship (Sandwich p-value, 0.6).
